Adobe Systems Inc. (ADBE) , the largest
maker of graphic-design software, approved a plan to buy back as
much as $2 billion in shares through the end of fiscal 2015.  The company will buy stock in the open market and set up
structured repurchase agreements with third parties,  San Jose ,
California-based Adobe said in a statement. The new program,
approved by Adobeâ€™s board, is similar to an earlier plan to
repurchase $1.6 billion through the end of fiscal 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
